Now I see that `Opt_a_tosbitwise` at line 1118 uses `D->Rhs.A.Flags & LI_DIRECT` - it accesses the `.A` member of the `Rhs` but the CHECK in `Opt_a_tossub` at line 1377 accesses both `Rhs.A.Flags` and `Rhs.X.Flags`. Let me check `Opt_a_tossub` more carefully:

The `Opt_a_tossub` at line 1377 has:
```c
CHECK ((D->Rhs.A.Flags & D->Rhs.X.Flags & LI_DIRECT) != 0);
```

This CHECK is in `Opt_a_tossub` which is only in `FuncRegATable`. Its precondition validation in `RegAPreCondOk` only checks `RhsLo->Flags & LI_DIRECT` (which is `D->Rhs.A.Flags`), not `D->Rhs.X.Flags`.

The fix needs to be in `RegAPreCondOk`. Looking at the code structure, the `_DIRECT` flags are checked in the `OP_RHS_LOAD_DIRECT` part of the if-else chain. But `RegAPreCondOk` doesn't track `LhsHi` and `RhsHi` at all.

Now, looking at `Opt_a_tosbitwise` (line 1118):
```c
if ((D->Rhs.A.Flags & LI_DIRECT) == 0) {
```
and `Opt_a_tossub` (line 1377):
```c
CHECK ((D->Rhs.A.Flags & D->Rhs.X.Flags & LI_DIRECT) != 0);
```

The `Opt_a_tossub` function checks both A and X have `LI_DIRECT`, while `Opt_a_tosbitwise` only checks A's `LI_DIRECT`. The fix should be in `RegAPreCondOk` to also check `LI_DIRECT` for the X register (high byte).

Looking back at `PreCondOk` for comparison:
```c
// Lines 1606-1615: OP_LHS_LOAD check
if ((Desc->Flags & OP_LHS_LOAD) != 0) {
    if ((LhsLo->Flags & LhsHi->Flags & LI_LOAD_INSN) == 0) {
        break;
    } else if ((Desc->Flags & OP_LHS_LOAD_DIRECT) != 0) {
        if ((LhsLo->Flags & LhsHi->Flags & LI_DIRECT) == 0) {
            break;
        }
    }
}
// Lines 1617-1626: OP_RHS_LOAD check  
if ((Desc->Flags & OP_RHS_LOAD) != 0) {
    if ((RhsLo->Flags & RhsHi->Flags & LI_LOAD_INSN) == 0) {
        break;
    } else if ((Desc->Flags & OP_RHS_LOAD_DIRECT) != 0) {
        if ((RhsLo->Flags & RhsHi->Flags & LI_DIRECT) == 0) {
            break;
        }
    }
}
```

So `PreCondOk` checks both Lo and Hi for LOAD and LOAD_DIRECT.

But `RegAPreCondOk` only checks Lo (which maps to `.A`):
```c
// Lines 1774-1783
if ((Desc->Flags & OP_RHS_LOAD) != 0) {
    if ((RhsLo->Flags & LI_LOAD_INSN) == 0) {
        break;
    } else if ((Desc->Flags & OP_RHS_LOAD_DIRECT) != 0) {
        if ((RhsLo->Flags & LI_DIRECT) == 0) {
            break;
        }
    }
}
```

The fix is to add `LhsHi` and `RhsHi` tracking in `RegAPreCondOk`, and use them in the `_DIRECT` checks. But wait - we need to figure out what the "Hi" corresponds to in the RegA context. In the RegA path, the X/high part of both LHS and RHS are the same value (that's why `SameRegXValue` was true). The `.A` corresponds to `Lo` and `.X` corresponds to `Hi`.

Let me now fix this. The fix is to modify `RegAPreCondOk` to also check the high byte (`.X`) for `LI_DIRECT`:

